{\ri30 \li30 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Under statute providing a basis for juvenile court jurisdiction if the child has suffered, or there is a substantial risk the child will suffer, serious physical harm or illness caused by the parent\rquote s failure or inability to adequately supervise or protect the child, a jurisdictional finding requires: (1) neglectful conduct by the parent in one of the specified forms; (2) causation; and (3) serious physical harm or illness to the minor, or a substantial risk of such harm or illness. 
}
