Juvenile court\rquote s finding that mother and child were not communicating, in sustaining dependency petition based on mother\rquote s \u8220\'3finability to adequately supervise or protect the child,\u8221\'3f was not supported by substantial evidence, where the record showed that mother and child were in daily telephone contact, and the county child welfare agency\rquote s jurisdiction/disposition report noted as a family strength that there was \u8220\'3fopen communication between the mother and the child, despite the current circumstances.\u8221\'3f 
}
