}\b0 \cf28 \f6 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 }}
{\b0 \cf1 \f6 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (300(b)) provides that a child comes within the jurisdiction of the juvenile court if: \u8220\'3fThe child has suffered, or there is a substantial risk that the child will suffer, serious physical harm or illness, 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f6 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f6 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
as a result of the failure or inability of his or her parent or guardian to adequately supervise or protect the child,
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f6 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 or the willful or negligent failure of the child\rquote s parent or guardian to adequately supervise or protect the child from the conduct of the custodian with whom the child has been left, or by the willful or negligent failure of the parent or guardian to provide the child with adequate food, clothing, shelter, or medical treatment, or by the inability of the parent or guardian to provide regular care for the child due to the parent\rquote s or guardian\rquote s mental illness, developmental disability, or substance abuse.\u8221\'3f (Italics added.) The italicized phrase is at issue on this appeal.
\par 
}
}
}
}
